reviews.text: Clean and peaceful by the time I visited it (1 PM)

I take the Hammersmith & City line to work during weekday. I love my commute into work because of “Tanike Kypist” (the lady who announces the different trains coming into the platform, she stands out in the platform whether it is raining, snowing or the weather is piping hot), I can hear Tanike’s jolly voice from across the bridge and rush into the station - if I hear my train. Thank you for helping the travellers at Whitechapel Station.

They don't know about their head. Train to Upminster was running and they said is not. They put people on different routes for no reason. 
They should find a way to realize how incompetent they are.
WAKE UP AND DO YOUR JOB

London Overground and Underground Station. Direct trains to West Croydon. The Station has recently been renovated with lots of upgrades, as old East London line became London Overground with extensions and connectivity. Underground services runs District and Hammersmith & City, and Metropolitan lines.
Thankfully, I always get help from friendly people around me but all in all, especially for people in wheelchairs it has to be barrier-free.
